Four species are under some protection category of the NOM-059; three are subject to special protection (
 Parabuteo unicinctus (Temminck, 1824); 
 Falco peregrinus Tunstall, 1771; 
 Aimophila notosticta (P. L. Sclater & Salvin, 1868)) and one is considered threatened (
 Geothlypis tolmiei (J. K. Townsend, 1839)). In total, 59 species are resident and 30 migratory; 43 are insectivorous, 14 omnivorous, 13 granivorous, seven nectarivores, seven carnivorous, and five frugivorous.
